         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">26/10/88 ¶  ¶ This is a real day of jubilation for me, noble Friend, through the arrival of the beautiful revision of certain orthopteran groups through your and Professor Hofmann's agency by the exce...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">88.10.26</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Ferdinand von Krauss</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Staatliches Museum für Naturkunde, Stuttgart.</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style=""/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotations by Krauss: 'Empf. 18. Dec. Rep. 4 Febr. 89' [Received 18 Dec. Replied 4 Febr 89] (letter not found); 'erhalt 2. Dec. 88 Sep. Abdr. Considerat phytog expressions. 10 Dec. Samen v. Patersonia.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Spinnen</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>zur bestimmen an Graf Keyserling [Eugen von Keyserling (1833-88)] in Glogau Ob nicht Menura Victoriae Balg zu bekommen.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>Ei haben wir v ihm Dank an French'. [Received 2 Dec.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>88 reprint of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Consideration of phytographica expressions</seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>10 Dec.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>seeds of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Patersonia</seg>.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Spiders<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to determine to Graf Keyserling in Glogau. Whether to get some<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Menura victoriae</seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>skins. We have eggs of it. Thanks to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[Charles]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>French<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[Snr]].<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                  </p>
               </note>26/10/88</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Dies ist ein wahrer Jubeltag für mich, edler Freund, durch die Ankunft der schönen Bearbeitung gewisser Orthopteran-Gruppen durch Ihre u Hr. Prof Hofmann’s Vermittlung von dem ausgezeichneten Hr Brunner von Wattenwyl. Sagen Sie diesem augsgezeichneten Gelehrten meinen besten Dank für dieser schätzbaren Beiträge zur Insekten Fauna Australiens, welche Arbeit ja für alle Zeiten hohe Werth haben wird. Ich will mich bemühen weitere Materialien aus diesen Insekten Gruppen zu erlangen. Bin ganz stolz darauf, auch mit dieser Thier-Gruppe meinen Namen identificirt zu sehen.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Endlich ist es gelungen einige wenige Leipoa Exemplare zu erlangen. Die armen unschuldigen Thiere werden wohl bald das Geschick der Alca impennis theilen. Man gönnt ihnen nicht den letzten Zufluchtsort in den entlegensten Wüsten, einfach um den Vogel zu verspeisen, trotz der Eier, die doch zum Theil zur Nahrung genommen werden könnten. Ich sende zwei. Sollten diese beide<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont">♂</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">oder<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont">♀</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">sein, so würde ich bitten eins an das Museum in Braunschweig an unsern Freund Prof. Blasius abzugeben. Etwas mehr Insekten-Material folgt auch diesmal wieder mit.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Immer Ihr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               </seg>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">26/10/88</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This is a real day of jubilation for me, noble Friend, through the arrival of the beautiful revision of certain orthopteran groups through your and Professor Hofmann's agency by the excellent Mr Brunner von Wattenwyl. Give my best thanks to this excellent savant for this valuable contribution to the insect fauna of Australia, which work will have high value indeed for all time. I intend to endeavour to obtain further<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>material of these insect groups. I am quite proud to see my name also identified with this group of animals.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Brunner von Wattenwyl<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(1888)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>had named<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Eremus muelleri</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in M's honour (p. 378), the collecting location being given as 'Queensland'.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>At last I have succeeded in obtaining some few<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Leipoa</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>specimens.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mound-building bird, commonly called 'Mallee fowl'.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The poor innocent creatures will probably soon share the fate of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Alca impennis</seg>.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Great Auk, rendered extinct earlier in the nineteenth century through depredations by collectors.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>They are not granted the last sanctuary in the most remote desert, simply to consume the birds, in spite of the eggs<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that surely could be taken in part for food. I send two. Should these both be<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont">♂</seg>or<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont">♀</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I would ask you to give one to the museum in Braunschweig to our friend Professor Blasius. As well some more insect material also follows again this time.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Always your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
